A 19-year-old boy, Tope Anisere has been charged before an Ado Ekiti Magistrate’s Court for sexually abusing a 3-year-old girl (names withheld) The accused person who is standing trial on a charge of indecent assault was accused of fondling the little girl. He was alleged to have committed the offence on 3rd January, 2020 in Otun Ekiti, Moba Local Government Area. The accused, according to the police prosecutor, Sergeant Olubu Apata, put the toddler on his laps and romanced her without penetration. Apata said it was the girl that reported the accused to her mother which led to his arrest. The prosecution who said the offence contravened Section 360 of the Criminal Code, Laws of Ekiti State, 2012  urged the court to adjourn the case to enable him study the file and assemble his witnesses. The accused pleaded not guilty to the charge read to him. His counsel, Mr. Abiola Gboyega, urged the court to grant his client bail and promised that the defendant would not jump bail. The Magistrate, Mrs. Kehinde Awosika, granted bail to the accused in the sum of N50,000 with one surety. Awosika who said the surety shall be a blood relation to the accused subsequently adjourned the case till February 10 for hearing.